##
##argcom
##
@node argcom "Argument commands"

 These commands cover the use of arguments plus the running of compiled
 programs, as well as the use of the Arguments requestor etc.

	COMMAND:	GETARGS
	DESCRIPTION:	GETARGS opens the arguments requestor for the user
			to choose which arguments are to be passed to their
			compiled program when run.
			This will only open the requestor if RUN has
			already been set.
	USAGE:		GETARGS

	COMMAND:	SETENVIRONMENT
	DESCRIPTION:	SETENVIRONMENT denotes which environment you wish
			to run your compiled program in, Either Cli or WB,
			If no argument is passed, It assumes WB.
	USAGE:		SETENVIRONMENT [type]

	COMMAND:	SETCLIARGS
	DESCRIPTION:	SETCLIARGS denotes the arguments that are to be
			passed to the compiled program when run in a CLI
			environment.
	USAGE:		SETCLIARGS <argument string>

	COMMAND:	SETWBARGS
	DESCRIPTION:	SETWBARGS denotes the arguments that are to be
			passed to the compiled program when run in a WB
			environment.
	USAGE:		SETWBARGS <argument 1> [argument 2]...[argument 15]

	COMMAND:	CLOSEARGSWINDOW
	DESCRIPTION:	CLOSEARGSWINDOW will close the argument requestor,
			but is only of use OUTSIDE the script that called
			GETARGS as that script then waits for the argument
			requestor to close before continuing.
	USAGE:		CLOSEARGSWINDOW

	COMMAND:	RESETARGS
	DESCRIPTION:	RESETARGS will clear the arguments back to
			the default values
	USAGE:		RESETARGS

	COMMAND:	CANCELARGS
	DESCRIPTION:	CANCELARGS will return the argument values to those
			that were SNAPPED using the command SNAPARGS, If
			the requestor was opened by another script, The
			values in use prior to the requestor will be used.
	USAGE:		CANCELARGS

	COMMAND:	SNAPARGS
	DESCRIPTION:	This will snapshot the current state of argument
